      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(kimi): show code quota in usage status",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds Kimi Code usage reporting to the existing provider usage pipeline.\n\n- Adds a Kimi usage fetcher for `GET https://api.kimi.com/coding/v1/usages`.\n- Parses Kimi Code `5h` and `7d` quota windows into the existing usage snapshot shape.\n- Wires the bundled `kimi-coding` provider into `resolveUsageAuth` and `fetchUsageSnapshot`.\n- Maps `kimi-code` and `kimi-coding` usage aliases to the new `kimi` usage provider.\n\n## Why\n\nKimi Code subscription users currently do not see quota usage in OpenClaw status surfaces. This is a focused follow-up to #67593.\n\nA previous broader attempt in #20343 also tried to add Kimi/Moonshot usage, but it mixed unrelated quota UI and provider changes and was closed unmerged. This PR keeps scope limited to Kimi Code usage integration so `/status`, provider usage summaries, and plugin usage hooks can show the Kimi Code quota windows without changing unrelated providers or UI grouping behavior.\n\n## Behavior\n\nWhen a Kimi API key is available from the provider config/store or `KIMI_CODE_API_KEY`, `KIMI_API_KEY`, `KIMICODE_API_KEY`, or `MOONSHOT_API_KEY`, OpenClaw can fetch the Kimi Code usage payload and display:\n\n- `5h` from the matching limit entry, using either label-based matching or duration metadata.\n- `7d` from the top-level `usage` row.\n\nThe fetcher supports both `used/limit` and `remaining/limit` shapes and returns stable usage errors for auth failures or malformed responses.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** Kimi Code subscription quota usage should be fetched through the new Kimi provider usage integration and normalized into the existing OpenClaw provider usage snapshot, so status/usage surfaces can show the Kimi `5h` and `7d` windows instead of omitting Kimi.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Local macOS OpenClaw checkout on PR branch `codex/kimi-code-usage-quota` at commit `fef2df50`, using the real local OpenClaw config at `/Users/alex/.openclaw/openclaw.json` with provider `kimi-coding` base URL `https://api.kimi.com/coding` and a real Kimi Code API key from config. Token redacted.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Ran a local Node command with `node --import tsx` that imported this PR's `./src/infra/provider-usage.fetch.kimi.ts`, read the local OpenClaw Kimi provider config, and called `fetchKimiUsage(token, 10000, fetch, { baseUrl })` against the real Kimi Code usage endpoint.\n\n**Evidence after fix:** Terminal output from the live command after this patch:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"proof\": \"real Kimi Code usage endpoint via PR fetchKimiUsage\",\n  \"startedAt\": \"2026-06-13T09:25:23.283Z\",\n  \"finishedAt\": \"2026-06-13T09:25:23.435Z\",\n  \"baseUrl\": \"https://api.kimi.com/coding\",\n  \"provider\": \"kimi\",\n  \"displayName\": \"Kimi\",\n  \"windows\": [\n    {\n      \"label\": \"5h\",\n      \"usedPercent\": 8\n    },\n    {\n      \"label\": \"7d\",\n      \"usedPercent\": 3\n    }\n  ],\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"token\": \"<redacted>\"\n}\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** The real Kimi Code endpoint returned a successful `kimi` usage snapshot with `displayName: \"Kimi\"`, parsed quota windows `5h: 8%` and `7d: 3%`, and `error: null`. This verifies the PR's live fetcher can authenticate with a real Kimi Code setup and normalize live endpoint output into the provider usage shape consumed by OpenClaw status/usage surfaces.\n\n**What was not tested:** Full UI rendering was not exercised; this proof covers the live provider usage fetch path and parsed snapshot used by the status/usage pipeline.\n## Validation\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- `COREPACK_HOME=/tmp/corepack corepack pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 docs/.generated/plugin-sdk-api-baseline.sha256 extensions/kimi-coding/index.ts extensions/kimi-coding/index.test.ts src/infra/provider-usage.fetch.ts src/infra/provider-usage.fetch.kimi.ts src/infra/provider-usage.fetch.kimi.test.ts src/infra/provider-usage.load.test.ts src/infra/provider-usage.shared.ts src/infra/provider-usage.shared.test.ts src/infra/provider-usage.types.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-usage.ts`\n- `COREPACK_HOME=/tmp/corepack corepack pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check`\n- `COREPACK_HOME=/tmp/corepack corepack pnpm plugin-sdk:check-exports`\n- `COREPACK_HOME=/tmp/corepack corepack pnpm vitest run src/infra/provider-usage.fetch.kimi.test.ts src/infra/provider-usage.shared.test.ts src/infra/provider-usage.load.test.ts extensions/kimi-coding/index.test.ts`\n- `COREPACK_HOME=/tmp/corepack corepack pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `COREPACK_HOME=/tmp/corepack corepack pnpm tsgo:extensions`\n\nNote: full-repo `pnpm format:check` currently reports existing formatting drift on upstream main outside this PR's files, so this PR was validated with targeted `oxfmt --check` for the changed files.\n",
